<div class="container">
    <h1>Organizations Supporting Neurodivergent Inclusion</h1>

    <div class="organization">
        <div class="logo">
            <a href="https://autisticadvocacy.org/" target="_blank">
                <img src="https://autisticadvocacy.org/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/ASAN-logo-sm-pkkav3p0lhtl5pji4glo1k7t2fj415qpycass565cw.png" alt="ASAN Logo">
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            <h2><a href="https://autisticadvocacy.org/" target="_blank">1. Autistic Self Advocacy Network (ASAN)</a></h2>
            <p><strong>Mission:</strong> ASAN is led by neurodivergent individuals. They work to empower neurodivergent people to make their own decisions and advocate for their rights.</p>
            <p><strong>What They Do:</strong> ASAN provides an abundance of resources for self-advocacy, offer guidance on policy reform, and promote societal acceptance of neurodiversity.</p>
            <p class="impact"><strong>Unique Factor:</strong> ASAN is run entirely by individuals on the spectrum, offering a truly authentic voice for the neurodivergent community.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="organization">
        <div class="logo">
            <a href="https://neurodiversityintheworkplace.org/" target="_blank">
                <img src="https://nitw.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/NEW_nitw_header-logo.png" alt="Neurodiversity in the Workplace Logo">
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            <h2><a href="https://neurodiversityintheworkplace.org/" target="_blank">2. Neurodiversity in the Workplace</a></h2>
            <p><strong>Mission:</strong> NITW help organizations create employment opportunities for neurodivergent individuals.</p>
            <p><strong>What They Do:</strong> NITW works with companies to create more inclusive hiring practices, provide job coaching, and offer specially tailored training to help integrate neurodivergent individuals into the workplace.</p>
            <p class="impact"><strong>Unique Factor:</strong> NITW focuses exclusively on connecting neurodivergent individuals with employers. They work to reshape workplaces to better support neurodiversity and promote long term career success.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="organization">
        <div class="logo">
            <a href="https://thearc.org/" target="_blank">
                <img src="https://thearc.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ArcLogo_Color_Rev_PNG_WEB.png" alt="The Arc Logo">
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            <h2><a href="https://thearc.org/" target="_blank">3. The Arc</a></h2>
            <p><strong>Mission:</strong> The Arc advocates for the rights of people with intellectual and developmental disabilities (IDD).</p>
            <p><strong>What They Do:</strong> The Arc provides support services, legal advocacy, and many other resources to promote inclusion and accessibility in education, employment, and daily life.</p>
            <p class="impact"><strong>Unique Factor:</strong> The Arc is one of the largest organizations that serves people with intellectual disabilities. They also offer a powerful voice for inclusion on a national level. Their vast reach allows them to influence policies on a broad scale.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

