        <div class="info">
            <h2><a href="https://www.understood.org/" target="_blank">4. Understood.org</a></h2>
            <p><strong>Mission:</strong> Understood empowers people with differences in learning and thinking, such as ADHD and dyslexia, to thrive in education and life.</p>
            <p><strong>What They Do:</strong> Understood provides resources for parents, educators, and individuals that supports learning needs, offers insights on inclusive education, and helps build stronger communities for neurodivergent individuals.</p>
            <p class="impact"><strong>Unique Factor:</strong> Understood focuses on personalized and accessible resources making Understood an essential platform for families facing learning and attention challenges.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="organization">
        <div class="logo">
            <a href="https://www.ncld.org/" target="_blank">
                <img src="https://www.ncld.org/wp-content/themes/ncld/img/header-logo.svg" alt="NCLD Logo">
            </a>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            <h2><a href="https://www.ncld.org/" target="_blank">5. National Center for Learning Disabilities (NCLD)</a></h2>
            <p><strong>Mission:</strong> NCLD aims to improve the lives of 1 in 5 people with learning and attention difficulties.</p>
            <p><strong>What They Do:</strong> NCLD advocates for policies that promote proper education, conduct research to create best practices, and provides resources to help individuals overcome learning disabilities in school and life.</p>
            <p class="impact"><strong>Unique Factor:</strong> NCLD's policy work on educational reform ensures that students with learning disabilities receive the support they need for success.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <p>“Inclusion stars with understanding and support. These organizations lead the way in empowering neurodivergent individuals.”</p>
